<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOXING; BORBOA MAKES SIXTH DEFENSE OF IBF TITLE AT FORUM TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Julio Cesar Borboa, who emerged from obscurity last year to capture the 
International Boxing Federation super-flyweight championship, makes the sixth 
defense of his belt tonight at the Forum against undefeated challenger Harold 
Grey. 
</P>
<P>
 Considering his dominance of the super-flyweight division, Borboa (23-4, 21 
knockouts), whose last outing at the Forum was a blistering fourth-round 
technical knockout of Jorge Luis Roman on April 25, is eyeing a move down to 
flyweight should he defeat Grey (16-0, 15 KOs). 
</P>
<P>
 The two most prominent fighters in the lighter divisions are light-flyweights 
Humberto (Chiquita) Gonzalez and Michael Carbajal. Borboa is hoping to meet one 
or both at flyweight. 
</P>
<P>
 "I feel at 112 (the flyweight limit), moving down to fight any of the great 
fighters, Chiquita or Carbajal, shouldn't be any problem," Borboa said. "I 
think that's where the big money will be -- at 112. 
</P>
<P>
 "The opportunity to fight at 115 (the super-flyweight limit) really came as a 
surprise. I'm really a flyweight." 
</P>
<P>
 Also on the card, which celebrates Forum Boxing's 12th anniversary, are two 
featherweight 10-rounders: Arnulfo (Chico) Castillo vs. Panchito Valdez; and 
Jesse Magana vs. Ericel Nucamendi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
