<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: CHOATE NAMED EXECUTIVE AT FCB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mark Choate has been appointed executive vice president and executive creative 
director of FCB Orange County in Santa Ana.He becomes the senior executive 
responsible for the creative product on the Mazda Motor of America account. 
Choate succeeds Larry Kopald, who is leaving in October. Choate was previously 
senior vice president and group creative director for D'Arcy Masius Benton & 
Bowles in St. Louis, with responsibility for the Anheuser-Busch Inc. account. 
Before that, he was vice president and creative director at FCB Chicago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
