PREP FOOTBALL '94 / CENTURY LEAGUE; CANYON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993 RECORDS OVERALL: 6-3-2 LEAGUE: 2-2-1 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL Bob Hughes: 6-3-2 03,20,05,05 RETURNING STARTERS OFF 
DEF 3 1 04,26,05,07,05 TOP RETURNERS OFF DEF YR Mike Beisner, 6-1, 205 -- DE/LB 
Sr. Adam Hoover, 6-1, 185 QB -- Sr. Greg Jacobs, 5-10, 175 WR -- Sr. Ryan 
McGonigal, 5-9, 150 WR -- Sr. Troy Mills, 5-11, 170 WR DB Jr. K.C. Pelle, 6-2, 
200 RB DB Sr. Joe Petronis, 6-2, 200 OL LB Sr. Matt Pond, 5-11, 170 -- DE Sr. 
Tim Tynan, 6-1, 185 WR -- Sr. 04,27,05,05,05 TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR Greg 
Baudot, 6-1, 185 OL DE Jr. Chris Carmona, 6-0, 175 TB LB Jr. Justin Giorgio, 
5-10, 170 TB DB Jr. Cory Mayne, 6-1, 230 OL DL Jr. Mike Tomarelli, 6-1, 175 QB 
-- So. Larry Witt, 5-11, 170 WR DB Sr. OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon backed into the playoffs, going 0-2-1 in its last three league games. 
But the Comanches got in for the first time since 1986. Getting back is going 
to take some doing. The Comanches have experience and some talent at skill 
positions, but the offensive line needs to be rebuilt. Petronis, a second-team 
all-league pick, is the only returning starter. Hoover, a first-team all-league 
pick, is back at quarterback to guide the run-and-shoot offense, which was 
erratic last season. Still, Hoover passed for more than 1,700 yards and 11 
touchdowns last season. Jacobs, a two-time all-league selection, caught 40 
passes last season. The offense will have to put some points up because the 
defense has huge holes to fill. Petronis is the only returning starter there. 
SCHEDULE 
</P>
