<TEXT>
<P>
 Macy-Federated Merger: Californians will get their first glimpse this week of 
a consolidation plan for Federated Department Stores and R.H. Macy & Co., the 
New York-based retailer that operates the Bullock's and I. Magnin chains in 
Southern California. Cincinnati-based Federated is expected to file the plan -- 
known as a disclosure statement -- in a New York Bankruptcy Court on 
Thursday.The statement will include references to plans for combining 
operations. However, full details on possible store closings, store conversions 
and layoffs are expected to be included in amendments filed in September. 
Federated, which will eliminate duplicative administrative operations when the 
companies merge, is expected to eliminate some jobs at San Francisco-based 
Macy's West, the regional headquarters for Macy. Some analysts also expect 
Federated to close some I. Magnin stores in Southern California. Federated 
plans to combine the operations of the two companies by December. 
