<TEXT>
<P>
 Some Foreign Firms to Get Tax Refunds: China has begun to refund taxes to 
about one-third of its foreign-funded ventures that have been hurt by a new tax 
system, the New China news agency said. Foreign-funded firms approved by 
authorities before Dec. 31 will get rebates for their increased tax burden for 
up to five years, the agency reported. One-third of foreign-funded ventures are 
hurt by a new tax system, including a value added tax, which went into effect 
this year, while one-third gained from it, said Dong Shukui, deputy director of 
the State Administration of Taxation's tax department. 
