<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: HONG KONG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GDP Forecast Raised: The government is now forecasting that economic growth 
this year, as measured by gross domestic product figures, will be 5.7%.The 
figure, released in its half-yearly economic report, is based on a revised 
formula for calculation that takes into account structural change in the 
economy. Under the old formula, the government had been forecasting GDP growth 
of 5.5% for 1994. Using the new method, Hong Kong's GDP growth has been revised 
upward to 5.9% in 1993 from a previous estimate of 5.6%, and 6.0% in 1992 
against 5.6% before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
