<HEADLINE>
<P>
AT LEAST 50 DEAD IN MOLDOVA FLOODS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Severe flooding in the former Soviet republic of Moldova has killed at least 
50 people and caused massive damage, Prime Minister Andrei Sangheli said 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The central part of the republic has already been declared a disaster zone, 
and the death toll appears likely to rise as rescuers reach more villages. 
</P>
<P>
 About 2,000 houses were damaged, roads were destroyed, hundreds of cattle 
drowned and crops were ruined in central and southern Moldova as a result of 
heavy rains, Deputy Prime Minister Valeriu Bulgari said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bulgari estimated the damage at $50 million, the Russian Interfax news agency 
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
