<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 2 DIE, SEVERAL HURT IN AUTO ACCIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two motorists died Sunday in separate automobile accidents, county authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first incident, an 18-year-old Oxnard man died at about 6:45 a.m. after 
the car in which he was riding collided with another automobile near the 
intersection of Pleasant Valley and Hailes roads, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Israel Perez died at the scene following the 6 a.m. accident in unincorporated 
area of the county near Oxnard, said Deputy Coroner Craig Stevens. 
</P>
<P>
 Stevens said that several people in both cars were injured when the two cars 
collided, but their conditions were not released. None of the motorists were 
wearing seat belts, Stevens said. 
</P>
<P>
 The second fatality occurred about 10 hours later on California 126 at Briggs 
Road near Santa Paula around 5 p.m., according to the California Highway 
Patrol. But the CHP had no details or names. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
