<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIGHT ALLEGEDLY ESCALATES TO ATTEMPTED MURDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fistfight between two men outside a Ventura convenience store escalated to 
attempted murder early Sunday when one of the men pulled a gun and fired 
several shots as he chased the other man for several blocks, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the incident outside the Circle K store at 1007 E. Main 
St. just after midnight, Ventura police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Joseph Michael Ransome, 26, and Anthony Pech, 23, fought outside 
the market. But when Pech began to lose the fistfight, he pulled out a handgun 
and began chasing Ransome, according to investigators. 
</P>
<P>
 Ransome avoided at least three rounds, including one bullet that struck a 
cinder-block wall just above his head, showering him in concrete fragments, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Accounts from witnesses led police to a nearby residence. The handgun 
allegedly used by Pech was found in a patch of shrubbery near the house, police 
said. It had been reported stolen to the Port Hueneme Police Department earlier 
this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Pech on suspicion of attempted murder and possession of stolen 
property, officials said. He was being held at Ventura County Jail in lieu of 
$250,000 bail and is scheduled to be arraigned Tuesday. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
