<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: UNION ENDORSES 5 ELECTION CANDIDATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A labor union that represents 6,000 public and private workers in Ventura 
County has announced its endorsements for the November election. 
</P>
<P>
 The Service Employees International Union, Local 998, endorsed Trudi Loh for 
supervisor in the 2nd District, Scott Montgomery for supervisor in the 4th 
District and Tom Mahon for auditor-controller. 
</P>
<P>
 Also getting the union's support is Democrat Mindy Lorenz in the race for the 
35th Assembly District seat and Democrat Jack O'Connell in the race for the 
18th Senate District. 
</P>
<P>
 The union made its choices after interviewing candidates, said Barry Hammitt, 
an executive with the labor group. KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
