condition after surgery Sunday with a gunshot wound to his upper thigh, said 
Sgt. Kevin McKeown of the Fountain Valley Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 His wound is not expected to be life threatening, McKeown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy was shot at about 11 p.m. after he and a group of friends left the 
Family Fun Center in the 9000 block of Recreation Circle and walked across the 
street to Tommy's Hamburgers, McKeown said. 
</P>
