 Four young males in a car approached the group and one of them opened fire 
with a handgun before fleeing north on Magnolia Avenue, McKeown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The wounded youth and his friends ran back across the street and he collapsed 
in the parking lot of the Fun Center, McKeown said. The incident is under 
investigation and police have asked any witnesses to the shooting to call the 
Police Department at (714) 965-4400. 
