<P>
 Champion ballroom dancers from around the world will compete and perform for 
the public during the 1994 Embassy Ballroom Dance Championships Friday through 
Sunday at the Red Lion Hotel, 3050 Bristol St., Costa Mesa. Competitions will 
begin each evening at 6:30 (doors open at 6) followed by exhibition 
performances at 11 p.m. Friday (with Marcus and Karen Hilton of London) and 
Saturday (with Donnie Burns and Gaynor Fairweather of Scotland) and 10:45 p.m. 
Sunday with winners in each dance category.The event is sanctioned by the 
National Dance Council of America. Tickets: $30 per day at the door. Advance 
reservations: (714) 963-9092. 
</P>
