105 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEATH PENALTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ted Bundy is a person that deserved and received his just reward.The excerpt 
from Polly Nelson's book "Defending the Devil" (Bookmark, Aug. 21) wanted us to 
show compassion to earthworms and Bundy. Well, Ms. Nelson, I think we did both. 
One, by executing Bundy we showed compassion for the victims and their 
families. Two, putting him in the ground keeps your lowly earthworms company. 
</P>
<P>
 Capital punishment is not barbaric if it was your daughter or son that was 
murdered. I want that avenue of justice always open in capital crimes. The 
endless appeals process should also be on death row. 
</P>
<P>
 SHANNON ARLON BURNS 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
